The '''Spacebarn''' was a [[Shipyard/Legends|shipyard]] on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]] owned and operated by [[Shug Ninx]], a [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] and master mechanic.

==History==
The facility was located deep under the spires of Nar Shaddaa, not far from the [[Corellian Sector (Nar Shaddaa)/Legends|Corellian Sector]]. The only way to enter the Spacebarn was to navigate a narrow tunnel called [[The Chute]]. Many smugglers and associates of Ninx's were welcome to use his facility to repair and modify their [[Starship/Legends|ships]]. The Spacebarn was where many smugglers, including [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], readied their craft prior to the [[Battle of Nar Shaddaa (4 BBY)|Battle of Nar Shaddaa]].

When [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] returned in a [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] body [[10 ABY/Legends|six years]] after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], Han Solo returned to Nar Shaddaa and met up with Shug Ninx. When [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] and [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]] appeared, violence ensued and Ninx lost a prized ship to collateral damage caused by Solo.

